Defines Configuration
\f1\b0 : Some libraries and tools use 
\f0\b\fs28 package.json
\f1\b0\fs32  to store configurations.Project configuration refers to the setup and organization of various elements that determine how a software project operates, behaves, and is built or deployed. It encompasses settings, parameters, and details that control different aspects of a project, from basic metadata to complex build processes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Overall, 
\f0\b\fs28 npm init
\f1\b0\fs32  is the foundational step to starting a new Node.js project, creating the essential 
\f0\b\fs28 package.json
\f1\b0\fs32  file, and setting the stage for managing dependencies and project configurations.\
