\f0\b\fs40 \cf2 1. Express\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 Express.js is a popular web application framework for Node.js. It provides a set of features and utilities to help developers build web servers and APIs. Key aspects of Express include:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Routing
\f1\b0 : Allows you to define routes (endpoints) for your server, including HTTP methods like GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Middleware
\f1\b0 : Supports middleware functions that can intercept and process HTTP requests and responses.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Templating and Static Files
\f1\b0 : Enables serving static files and integrating with templating engines like EJS or Handlebars.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Flexibility and Extensibility
\f1\b0 : Provides a flexible structure for building server-side applications.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Express is widely used to create RESTful APIs, web applications, and back-end services.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs40 \cf2 2. Mongoose\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 Mongoose is an Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) library for MongoDB, a NoSQL database. Mongoose makes it easier to interact with MongoDB by providing:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Schema Definition
\f1\b0 : Allows you to define data models with specific structures and data types.\
\ls8\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Validation and Middleware
\f1\b0 : Supports data validation rules and middleware functions for schema-level processing.\
\ls8\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Document-Oriented Operations
\f1\b0 : Simplifies CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations on MongoDB documents.\
\ls8\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Relationships
\f1\b0 : Provides features to model relationships between documents.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0
\cf2 With Mongoose, developers can work with MongoDB in a more structured and consistent way, making it easier to manage and query data.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs40 \cf2 3. CORS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) is a middleware package that handles cross-origin requests in Node.js applications. It enables or restricts HTTP requests from different origins (domains) to a server, controlling which origins are allowed to access server resources. CORS is essential for:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Web Security
\f1\b0 : Prevents unauthorized cross-origin requests and protects against common security vulnerabilities.\
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Enabling Cross-Origin Requests
\f1\b0 : Configures which origins, HTTP methods, and headers are allowed in cross-origin requests.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Using CORS, you can allow safe interactions between different domains while maintaining security.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs40 \cf2 4. Nodemon\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 Nodemon is a development utility that automatically restarts a Node.js application when changes are detected in the source code. It helps developers by:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Improving Development Workflow
\f1\b0 : Saves time by automatically reloading the application, allowing developers to see changes in real-time without manually restarting the server.\
\ls10\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Watching for File Changes
\f1\b0 : Monitors specific files or directories and triggers a restart when changes occur.\
\ls10\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Configurable
\f1\b0 : Allows customization of what files to watch, which extensions to monitor, and additional scripts to run before or after restarts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Nodemon is a common tool for enhancing productivity during Node.js development.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

